use Digest::HMAC_SHA1 qw( hmac_sha1 );
 
my $policy    = encode_base64($policy_document);
$policy       =~ tr{\n}\{}d ;   # remove end-of-lines, if any
my $signature = encode_base64(hmac_sha1($policy, $key));
$signature    =~ tr{\n}\{}d; # remove end-of-lines, if any
End-of-line removal is something I've seen in the Java and Ruby examples, but not in Python's. Is there any specific reason?

